<h1>Getting Started</h1>
<p>Welcome to Routely! This guide will help you get up and running with type-safe routing in minutes.</p>

<h2>Installation</h2>
<p>Install the core package:</p>
<pre><code>npm install @oxog/routely-core</code></pre>

<h2>Basic Setup</h2>
<p>Create your first router with a few routes:</p>
<pre><code>import { createRouter, route, Outlet } from '@oxog/routely-core';

// Define routes
const routes = [
  route('/', () => import('./pages/Home')),
  route('/about', () => import('./pages/About')),
  route('/users/:userId', () => import('./pages/UserDetail')),
];

// Create router
const router = createRouter({ routes });

// Use in your app
function App() {
  return (
    &lt;router.RouterProvider router={router}&gt;
      &lt;Outlet /&gt;
    &lt;/router.RouterProvider&gt;
  );
}</code></pre>

<h2>Defining Routes</h2>
<p>Routes are defined using the <code>route()</code> function:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Static routes:</strong> <code>route('/about')</code></li>
  <li><strong>Dynamic routes:</strong> <code>route('/users/:userId')</code></li>
  <li><strong>Nested routes:</strong> Pass children array as third argument</li>
</ul>

<h2>Navigation</h2>
<p>Use the <code>useNavigate()</code> hook for programmatic navigation:</p>
<pre><code>function MyComponent() {
  const navigate = useNavigate();
  
  return (
    &lt;button onClick={() => navigate('/about')}&gt;
      Go to About
    &lt;/button&gt;
  );
}</code></pre>

<h2>Accessing Parameters</h2>
<p>Use the <code>useParams()</code> hook with TypeScript generics for type safety:</p>
<pre><code>function UserDetail() {
  const { userId } = useParams&lt;{ userId: string }&gt;();
  
  return &lt;div&gt;User ID: {userId}&lt;/div&gt;;
}</code></pre>

